\f3\i\fs32 psi
\f0\i0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f2\fs32 . By common convention,  when pressure is given in psi, pounds per square foot, or similar units, gage pressure is assumed. The <q>g</q> (for gage) is added only when there is some possibility of confusion. Absolute pressure, on the other hand, is always expressed as pounds per square inch absolute (psia), pounds per square foot absolute (psfa), and so forth. \
